From dd1e6a2ff9f29f8206c554ef1ad854327159ccd5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 11:28:27 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Redesign linked notes as a structured block, popup-ify issue
 editing, trim Home and add sidebar counts

- Notes: replace inline [[wiki-link]] autocomplete with a structured
  Note.links field, a fixed "Notas Ligadas" block with a note picker
  (+ optional label) and a preview popup with an "Abrir nota" button;
  backlinks are now derived from the structured links instead of
  parsing note text
- Issues: clicking a row/card now opens the detail editor as a modal
  popup instead of an inline side panel
- Home: drop the "Today At A Glance" stat cards
- Sidebar: show item counts next to Notes, Voice Notes, Tasks, Tags
  and Artifacts
